      • getParseUnitFromLine

        public ILineContext getParseUnitFromLine(String inputLine,
                                         ILineContext context)
                                  throws ParseException
        Description copied from interface: IPreprocessor
        Gets the next complete parse unit from a single line of preprocessed input. The parse units are derived from the history of partial or incomplete statements observed so far, appended with the input line. The default behavior is to return the original input.

        The preprocessor may add lines back into the input history, for example from include directives.

        Specified by:
        getParseUnitFromLine in interface IPreprocessor
        Overrides:
        getParseUnitFromLine in class AbstractPreprocessor
        Returns:
        found statement, or null if no found statements.
        Throws:
        ParseException

        public boolean isPartialStatement()
        Description copied from interface: IPreprocessor
